




TY  - JOUR
T1  - Database Models and Managerial Intuition: 50% Model + 50% Manager
AU  - Blattberg, Robert C.
AU  - Hoch, Stephen J.
Y1  - 1990/08/01
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.36.8.887
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.36.8.887
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 887
EP  - 899
VL  - 36
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We focus on ways of combining simple database models with managerial intuition. We present a model and method for isolating managerial intuition. For five different business forecasting situations, our results indicate that a combination of model and manager always outperforms either of these decision inputs in isolation, an average R2 increase of 0.09 (16%) above the best single decision input in cross-validated model analyses. We assess the validity of an equal weighting heuristic, 50% model + 50% manager, and then discuss why our results might differ from previous research on expert judgment.
AB  - We focus on ways of combining simple database models with managerial intuition. We present a model and method for isolating managerial intuition. For five different business forecasting situations, our results indicate that a combination of model and manager always outperforms either of these decision inputs in isolation, an average R2 increase of 0.09 (16%) above the best single decision input in cross-validated model analyses. We assess the validity of an equal weighting heuristic, 50% model + 50% manager, and then discuss why our results might differ from previous research on expert judgment.
